---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About agentstack" description="Why this publication exists and how to read it.">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 tracking-tight">About agentstack</h1>

  <div class="prose max-w-2xl">
    <p class="text-lg">
      There is no good publication aimed at engineers <em>building</em> agent platforms.
      Existing content is either vendor-produced (biased) or consumer-oriented (too general).
      agentstack fills the gap — in-the-trenches content on harnesses, context, memory,
      integrations, and orchestration, backed by a systematic evaluation lab whose findings
      you can defend in a production design review.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">Why canon envelopes</h2>
    <p>
      Every lab finding is emitted as a canon envelope conforming to the
      <a href="https://synaplex.ai/discovery-framework/0.1.0/">discovery-framework spec</a> —
      an obligations model (not a state machine) that forces pre-registration, typed evidence,
      cited contradictions, and hash-bound artifacts. Fast blogs can out-publish us;
      they cannot out-replay us.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">Editorial independence</h2>
    <p>
      Sponsored evaluations exist and are priced. They use the <em>same</em> methodology
      pipeline as organic ones, run through the <em>same</em> adversarial review, and
      carry a cryptographic <code>Policy.provenance.sponsor</code> field in canon so the
      provenance is mechanically inspectable. Sponsors do not get preview or veto over
      findings. If that's not the kind of sponsorship a vendor wants, that's fine —
      we publish organic evaluations too.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">What we won't do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>1:1 consulting or audits. Everything we publish is one-to-many.</li>
      <li>Take vendor-provided benchmark numbers at face value.</li>
      <li>Retract an eval because a vendor asked politely.</li>
      <li>Bury a negative finding.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</Layout>
